Class IfStatement

java.lang.Object
  flowchart.IfStatement
All Implemented Interfaces:
AbstractStatement
public class IfStatement
extends java.lang.Object
implements AbstractStatement

A IF statement consists of a condition (denoted by a diamond) and one or two branches (represented by a StatementSequence respectively).

Version:
1.00 (Last update: June 8, 2008)
Author:
Dr. Wen-jun LI, Da LUO
